Hospital staff, Beijing Native Cao Guangchen and director of Wuhan Rong Jun Hospital

At the fuhe Toll Station

36 hours, 2,400 kilometers,

A Beijinger,

5,000 masks,

200 protective suits sent to Wuhan:

There are no heroes in the face of an epidemic

Narrator: Cao Guangchen

38, brand director

Beijing

Cao Guangchen, 38, is a native of Beijing. He is in self-isolation at his home in Beijing. He drove alone to Wuhan with 5,000 masks and 200 protective suits, returning to Beijing in the early hours of January 30.

From the first time he saw academician Zhong Nanshan's report, he began to pay close attention to the epidemic. However, the news of the city closure of Wuhan, let him really realize the seriousness of the situation. "The first reaction to that feeling was that SARS had come back again in my memory. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
5,000 masks hand-packed by Cao Guangchen and his close friends

Cao Guangchen did not have relatives, family members engaged in health care work, but a few doctor friends stick to the post. A few days later, they have contact Cao Guangchen borrow mask, when his hands only 3. "As the closure of the city inevitably aggravated the shortage of materials, Wuhan's friends were even more in a time of crisis. "

On Jan. 23, he contacted a mask manufacturer in Jilin through a friend and immediately ordered 5,000 KN95 masks to be donated to Wuhan in his own name. But the situation is urgent, and in time for the Spring Festival holiday, logistics can not be delivered in time. To get the supplies to Beijing, he drove to Liaoyuan on New Year's Eve, only to turn back when he reached the Beijing border.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Cao Guangchen (right) and his friends

At 10:00 p.m. on January 27th, all the supplies were loaded into the truck

On January 28, he repeated calls to customer service before agreeing to pick up the goods at a distribution center in Shunyi District, Beijing. "The masks weren't even boxed because they were shipped in such a hurry. I made a quick call to some friends in Beijing, and together we sorted and packed manually in Changping District. It wasn't loaded until late at night. "

Handwritten Letter of intent on individual donation by Cao Guangchen

Originally Cao Guangchen plan from Beijing medical fast-track delivery to Wuhan, but express delivery notice can arrive in a week. He decided to pick up the suit in Baoding and drive himself to Henan to deliver it.

Because there is no place to print during the Spring Festival, Cao wrote a donation book by hand and pressed his handprint in order to ensure the goods donated in his personal name could enter the green passage smoothly.

Cao Guangchen at the Xinyang service station in Henan

But accidents happen too fast. On his way to Henan, Cao Guangchen suddenly learned from the director of the Children's Wing Hospital in Wuhan that the materials could not be transferred in Henan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
SF Express helps pack and box for free

"As of January 24, there were less than 2,000 masks in the first-contacted va hospital, " Cao said. In order to meet the needs of first-line medical staff in Wuhan, Cao decided to drive to Wuhan himself. "I struggled internally, but the importance of timeliness trumped self-preservation. "

Many people heard the news, advised him to donate to the local hospital in Beijing, or encouraged him to resell, Cao Guangchen did not agree. "I have promised Wuhan Hospital that I will be entrusted by others and be loyal to them, " he told his parents as he drove to Wuhan alone, wearing 4,000 adult masks, 1,000 child masks and 200 protective suits.

Timeline:

Evening of 23 January: in-kind donation is planned;

January 24 noon: With the Red Cross and other hospitals failed to contact the case, the initiative to contact Wuhan Yi director to help contact the Wuhan Veterans Hospital, can make personal donations;

January 27: pick up and pack the goods in person at Shunyi District

Early in the morning of January 28: Personally to Shunfeng headquarters communication, but the goods can not be delivered in time to Wuhan, decided to personally go to Henan. Arrive in Baoding that night, add 200 dupont protective suits, sleep in the car that night;

January 29 am: set off in Henan, on the way that can not be delivered in Henan, immediately decided to drive to Wuhan;

January 29,15:00: entered the border of Hubei Province, 17:00 PM and Wuhan Veterans Hospital Director of the children finished delivery, return to Beijing;

At: A. M. on January 30, he arrived in Hengshui, Hebei Province, where he was released after a temperature check, and at 05:11 at his home in Beijing, where he has been quarantined since.

Route Chart

Share your location with the child officer near the drop point

A 12-hour drive from Wuhan to Beijing, 1,200 km. To avoid the spread of the virus, Cao had only a brief exchange with two people at a Hengshui checkpoint and one at a Fugou County gas station. I haven't met anyone since I came to Beijing.

Knowing that Cao Guangchen would personally deliver supplies to the epidemic area, many people gave him free help: SF provided many free cartons, Didi gave him a set of protective clothing, and the deputy director of the Wuhan Bureau of Commerce helped him get in touch with Wuhan Hospital, he promised to coordinate the fast-track to Wuhan if needed; Tong, director of the Wuhan Veterans Hospital, was eager to get in touch with him... "without them, I can't get these supplies to China smoothly. "

On the night of January 28th,

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Arrived in Baoding, picked up 200 suits, and spent the night in a camper

In fact, the money to buy masks, Cao Guangchen was originally intended to transform the rv with. Many people do not understand, and even hundreds of people in the wechat group publicly taunted him. But he only believes in one thing, money can no longer earn money, people no longer come back. Right and wrong, in the face of danger, should not be on the gains and losses.

When a reporter contacted Cao Guangchen, it was on his way back to Beijing from Wuhan. What he saw with his own eyes, he said, was not as serious as everyone thought. The closer we are to Wuhan, the closer we are to the truth, the more fearless we are. "What is more frightening than the spread of the epidemic is the spread of panic. "

Now that the supplies have arrived, it's a relief. Friends posted him on facebook as a hero. Cao Guangchen said: "there is no hero in front of the epidemic. I old Cao is just an ordinary person in a critical moment, to come forward. "

According to Cao, the situation on the front line is:

1. The grass roots in Wuhan are in great need of medical supplies. They can contact relevant hospitals, especially those that have not publicly asked for help. At that moment, the situation is already very critical

2. Other public officials, such as traffic police, still wear disposable face masks, and they also need to donate. Medical resources are likely to be even scarcer around Hubei and elsewhere. Right now, medical supplies are more useful than money.

I want to say to everyone: "You can prevent the virus, but do not discriminate against the sick. Go Wuhan! Go Hubei! Go China! "

Surgeons on the front line:

Worked so hard that he slept on the floor and curled up in a cupboard,

Is the norm for medical professionals

Narrator: Dr. Zhao

31, surgeon

Wuhan

Dr Zhao is a 31-year-old surgeon. At the moment, he is in a hospital in Wuhan, working for many days.

By the end of December 2019, many hospitals in Wuhan had admitted more than patients with pneumonia of unknown cause. Many hospitals, referring to the experience of SARS in 2003, have clearly sensed that this is not normal.

But before the city shut down, the public awareness of the epidemic and attention is not high, do not wear masks, do not do any protection of people everywhere.

Rescue workers arrive in Wuhan

The surgeons, on the other hand, were on the front lines of the reserve army in mid to late January 2020. His hospital, which has been discharging patients before they can be discharged years ago, is trying to reduce the number of residents. Zhao said: "In the absence of confirmation point before the hospital, fever clinic every day full of health care workers have been falling down with infection. "

The actual target hospital was in early January. Although there has been a slight decrease in the number of fever outpatients, the number of visits to designated hospitals has increased. The front-line personnel of infection department, aspiration department and Emergency Department were the first group infected in the hospital. In the later period, even the departments with weaker protection such as surgery also appeared the situation of successive infection.

The first day of the construction of Vulcan Mountain

"It can only be said that before the construction of Mount Vulcan and Mount Thor, there was no way to ensure that all suspected patients could be quarantined, observed and all confirmed patients could be admitted to the hospital. After all, there are too few beds and not enough first-line medical care. This is indeed the real situation,"Zhao said.

Wuhan under siege

People wait in line at a supermarket after the city was closed

After the city was closed, pedestrians and vehicles were barely visible on the streets, and everyone began to wear masks outside. Wuhan people from indifferent, to panic helpless again to the city, and all quickly into the fight against the new state of pneumonia, but also only a few days.

The five questions most frequently asked by family and friends as a doctor are:

1. The severity of the outbreak (infectious, case fatality?

2. How long will the outbreak last?

3. How to protect against new coronary pneumonia?

4. How do you treat new coronary pneumonia (medication, hospitalization) ?

5. What are the actions and actions of the Wuhan Government?

The branch of the hospital where Dr. Zhao is located is a designated hospital for fever, and all the medical staff who can take the top line have been taken to the top line in batches. Many medical staff have finished their vacation and rushed back to Wuhan.

First-line medical staff of Tongji Hospital

From Wuhan doctor's gnash teeth to insist, arrived from all directions "the reinforcement troops" , in the heart also unceasingly arouses the hope. "This is no longer a province or a city. This is a war for the whole country. "

Self-made protective glasses made by medical staff

The medical staff is the high-risk crowd, own infection, including the family member infection will hear, sees every day. Quarantine, testing, treatment, the process is the same as the general public.

And what you're going through now is a part of every paramedic's routine. Even if not in the face of this epidemic, in the daily work, continuous work to sleep on the floor, cabinets, are the normal health care workers.

"What I can tell you in detail is that after the closure of the city, there was a call in the hospital working group. All the doctors and nurses responded immediately without hesitation and obeyed the orders. No one hesitated or flinched. "

Relief supplies arrive at Tongji Hospital

Dr. Zhao said, in fact, his State of mind has not changed much, because see more life and death. This year feels like no new year, all heart in the fight against new pneumonia.

"It is important to remind everyone that in the face of an epidemic, there are so many rumors, and how to properly interpret the messages and comments received is something that everyone needs to identify. "

Liu Xiaoguang's house

On New Year's Eve, my father was in the hospital saving lives,

He took one of the most extraordinary family photographs

Narrator: Liu Xiaoguang

33, family photographer

On the eve of the Lunar New Year, Liu Xiaoguang, who lives in Wuhan, Hubei Province, canceled his family's New Year's dinner. The 33-year-old spent the most memorable New Year's eve of his life a few days ago.

All kinds of reports of the outbreak are flooding in on mobile phones. I could still hear the siren of the ambulance. On New Year's Eve, Liu Xiaoguang's family stayed apart. On the 22nd, the daughter and her wife returned to their native Xishui County to try to avoid infection. He and his mother are staying at home in Wuhan and have been afraid to go out.

His father, on the other hand, had been fighting in the Huimin Hospital in Wuhan for more than ten days. On New Year's Eve, when all three phones were switched on, Liu Xiaoguang, a family photographer, recorded the moment. "This is the most special family photo. "

Now, they skype with their father every day to check in. "My father has always been on the front line, in my eyes he is a soldier, he is fighting for Wuhan. "

"I used to be able to live my life without boundaries, " Liu Xiaoguang said. "Now I don't think of life as a personal matter. The family behind every health care worker is waiting for them to come back. "

The second day of the Lunar New Year, Wuhan, Hubei Province

Liu Xiaoguang's mother, across the window from the self imposed isolation

The fourth day of the Lunar New Year, Wuhan, Hubei

Liu Xiaoguang's house

During the outbreak, Liu Xiaoguang developed a low grade fever. During this time, any symptoms can be frightening, and fever is a big no-no. "What if something really happened to him? " So Liu Xiaoguang initiated a self-imposed quarantine at home. To be safe, mom wears a mask at home, too.

Now, the whole city is like an empty city. "This city has given me so many fond memories that even if there was an epidemic, I could not leave it. "

There are neighbors who have been diagnosed, and every day in his circle of friends, he sees the news of the death of some of his fellow citizens in Wuhan. Wuhan people always like to say "riveting must be done" , meaning either not to do, or do it well, which is perhaps the spirit of Wuhan people.

According to interviews with people in Hubei, the issues they are most concerned about are:

1. Since the number of people infected is increasing, when will the increase stop?

2. When will drugs and vaccines be developed to treat patients with new forms of pneumonia?

3. If the outbreak can not be controlled in a short time, when will the people of Hubei be able to return to work?

4. When will the migrant workers from other provinces leave Hubei? When can the people of Hubei Really Return Home?

5. Can the leadership of Hubei Province solve the problem?

Even so, they responded to the world and guarded the city in ways they thought were right:

Zhaorui Hotel, Wuhan, China

Guangdong medical team checking in

The 31 year old photographer, Moon, has been living in Wuhan. This year, she did not have New Year's Eve dinner with her parents. On the evening of the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, the family members in their own hotel, personally received the support of the Guangdong medical team to Wuhan. This is a voluntary reward from the Moon family trapped in this city.

In Wuhan Hospital

Taking their temperature every day is also one of their most important jobs

The day before New Year's Eve, Wuhan announced the closure of the city, when the epidemic situation became more serious. Wuhan People Cai Shu's relatives and friends are safe. But two of her best friends are nurses, and they're always on the front lines.

It's part of their job to protect themselves at this point.

January 28, Hanyang Hospital, Wuhan

Cai Shu's best friend, a nurse on the front line

Cai Shu and two in the first-line struggle in the girlfriends wechat group

They tell each other every day that they're okay

Her two best friends, one in the Hanyang Hospital, the other in the West Hospital of the Fourth Hospital. Three people have a wechat group, called "three friends" , before always talk about nothing, now, every day is two friends a day of food, drink, and physical conditions.

In special times, spiritual companionship and encouragement can always give you strength.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Due to lack of protective gear

The disposable protective clothing, after disinfection with ultraviolet light repeated use

The two men were in a hospital with limited protective resources. Wuhan Hanyang Hospital, lacking protective equipment, will use disposable protective clothing, ultraviolet disinfection and repeated use. Wuhan Four Hospitals West Hospital, spent 2 days to transform into an isolation ward, doctors, nurses can only be here for a moment of rest.

Every day in the group to see some of the first-line medical staff to send photos. The reception desk of the hospital will be filled with all kinds of food from strangers at any time.

No one ever leaves a name. They just leave something and then they leave.

24-hour Hazmat suits, ligature marks all over his face and hands. In order to avoid frequent toilet, they do not dare to eat too much food, do not dare to drink more water, lips are all cracks.

Cai Shu home filled with tension and panic, she stood at home balcony, looking at the window gloomy decadent scenery, feel like their own mood at the time, decided to use the camera to record.

Caishu love this "gave birth to her, raised her" city. Even though it's sick now, everyone's doing everything they can to cure it. "The greatest happiness in the world is the health and safety of those around you. "

Wuhan before the blockade

Leo Of Capricorn, December

After the closure of the city, the once bustling streets

Just a few passersby in masks

The Capricorn Lion is an insurance consultant in Wuhan. He took these photos while driving his wife to work after the city was sealed off.

It's hard to imagine 2020 Wuhan will be like this, home video instead of walking the streets. See still stick to the post of delivery boys, cleaners, will still be moved.

Traffic police on duty in Dangyang, Hubei Province

Yuan Xiaowen, 58, is a traffic policeman in Dangyang, Hubei Province. In order to check and persuade the passing vehicles, reduce the flow of people, contact, New Year's Day, he still stuck to the epidemic prevention and control duty stations in Takahashi.

Late on New Year's Day, Dangyang, Hubei

Yuen siu-man is on duty at an outbreak control station in Takahashi

This photo was taken at midnight. There were two confirmed cases in Dangyang, and no one was taking any chances! "Epidemic Prevention and control is the most important work at present. As police, it is our duty to stay on the job! "

To promote epidemic prevention in the community

The third day of Lunar New Year, Dangyang, Hubei Province

Liu Shimei, a community worker, is on duty

Liu Shimei, a 46-year-old community worker, has been on the streets every day since New Year's Eve, discouraging people from walking around and putting on masks.

January 22, Wuhan, Hubei Province

At Xlily's house

Family photographer Xlily was having dinner with her husband when she got a phone call from a friend who had asked her to buy a mask. The friend personally delivered it downstairs, the husband took it and put it in the corner of his desk, and Xlily took this picture.

This New Year, no longer hear the mother's nagging, children's playful voice... only the husband and wife each brush their mobile phones, occasionally exchange information, discuss the epidemic.

XLILY's husband is out shopping for ingredients

XLILY's husband is going to the supermarket downstairs to buy food because there aren't enough ingredients in the house. Before going out, he made a mask out of a plastic bag.

Xlily and her husband play badminton at home

January 29, Wuhan, Hubei Province

Xlily and her husband smashed all the walnuts in the house

On the left of the puzzle is a virus, and on the right is a man with a hammer

"We'll beat it eventually. "

XLILY and her husband

Returned my ticket home on January 20th

XLILY is a family photographer. She says she doesn't want to forget the special year of 2020.

She will certainly live a better life, love family, friends, take good care of their health, and these photos are the best proof and reminder.

A view of Yichang Street after the city was closed

Between the city and the street

When Dai Chao, a video photographer, arrived home in Yichang, Hubei Province, on January 19, the mood for the Lunar New Year was so strong that many people were happy to go out and buy New Year goods. "At the time, it was thought to be the most common flu of the cold. "

Today, the streets of Yichang remain mostly empty. Railways, airports and public transport are closed. Highways are all closed. Even the county area within the county and county, village and village are closed between the state of the road, set up all the checkpoints, there are special guards.

The stock of goods in the supermarket is adequate, but there are few buyers

Many supermarkets and drugstores are open for a short period of time and usually close around 3 pm. "A lot of people say it's been a magical year, like the end of the world... " supermarket shopping is also a good list in advance, quickly.

Yichang, daily disinfection

Radio will always remind everyone of the development of the epidemic, Dai Chao now even occasionally to the supermarket, but also put on a mask before going out, try to keep people at a distance. "We should recognize that we are fighting the virus, not the people of Hubei. We should not discriminate against the people of Hubei. "

Miaozui, Yichang, Hubei

Miao Miao, who worked in Shanghai after graduating from university, can only return to their hometown of Dangyang, Hubei Province, to be reunited with their parents during the Spring Festival.

New Year's Eve just arrived in Yichang East station, we learned that because of the epidemic, beginning at 6:00 on the first day of the new year, between Yichang and Dangyang state road, county road, provincial road may be blocked. Miao Miao's father, who had planned to leave the city at 3 am to pick her up, was on the road and, fearing the outbreak would get worse, decided to keep her in Yichang.

"If it gets worse, at least medical care in Shanghai will be better, " said Miao Miao, who is still separated from her parents.

January 31, Wuhan, Hubei Province

Photograph by XLILY

In the words of Xlily, thank you all for your courage and love! You use their own strength for Wuhan bear all, but also please take care of yourself, there are many people are looking forward to you go home.

Wuhan and Hubei are suffering from a rare epidemic disaster, no one can stay out of this battle, please continue to pay attention to a more follow-up report, and provide assistance within your capacity. I would like to pay tribute to all the "soldiers" in the front line of the epidemic!
